<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dearly" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dearly,</orth> 1) at a high price: <cit><quote>d. bought,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 100</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>riders d. hired,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>pay full d. for . . .,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 1, 84</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>as the upper Germany can d. witness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 3, 30</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>she hath bought the name of whore thus d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 128</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>held thee d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 102</bibl></cit> and <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 1, 36</bibl>.<lb />2) exquisitely: <cit><quote>man, how d. ever parted,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 96</bibl></cit> (== richly gifted). <cit><quote>rubies unparagoned, how d. they do't!</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 2, 18</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) heartily: <cit><quote>as we d. grieve for that which thou hast done,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.3.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 3, 43</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>most d. welcome,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 130</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 18</bibl>. <cit><quote>and greets your highness d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>how d. would it touch thee to the quick,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 132</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to adore d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 2, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to cherish d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 3, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to hate d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 35</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 42.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 42, 2</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.179" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 179</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 31</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.218" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 218</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.317" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 317</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 4, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 4, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 186</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.153" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 136</bibl> <cit><quote>to tender,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.77" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 2, 77</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 107</bibl>.
